<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="614" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d614">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">702.1211/1103: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Governor of the State of New York</hi>
                                (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Miller</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Albany</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-27"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                1922</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 6:50 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of 27th relative Mexico Central Administration received,
                            matter referred to Attorney General of the State to take immediate steps
                            to ascertain if purpose set forth can be accomplished. Advise you
                            later.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nathan L. Miller</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>